Purpose & context
José is building HIIT-Gym, a Portuguese-language fitness gym website deployed on Cloudflare Pages via the onitech38/HIIT-Gym GitHub repository. The project is a PWA built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, using Supabase for authentication and database, and an Anthropic API proxy via Cloudflare Pages Functions for a chat assistant widget.
José works with Claude as a senior front-end/back-end collaborator. Established coding conventions:

Pure CSS Nesting where hierarchy mirrors HTML structure
@layer usage for animations, media queries, and variables
Minimal JavaScript; warn when JS is being introduced
Simplest and cleanest solutions preferred
Step-by-step explanations for each change
Avoid JS when CSS can handle it

José has been direct about expecting thorough diagnosis before solutions are proposed — he explicitly called out repeated misdiagnoses and asked Claude to evaluate all possibilities before acting.

Current state
The site is live on Cloudflare Pages. Recent sessions resolved a series of cascading production bugs following a refactor that introduced global.js for shared functions. Key resolved issues include:

data.js and global.js load order fixed in index.html (must precede script.js)
Supabase CDN pinned to @2.49.4 across all four HTML files to avoid cached version incompatibility with newer key formats
functions/api/chat.js fixed: replaced destructured const { request, env } = context with direct context.env / context.request access to resolve Cloudflare bundler scope errors
Dead code and duplicate data declarations (coaches, modalidadesData) removed from script.js
Blog auth guard (pre-Supabase localStorage redirect) removed
Supabase handle_new_user trigger rebuilt with COALESCE to accept both camelCase and snake_case metadata fields
Service Worker cache bumped to v3.1 with corrected asset paths

Pending / unconfirmed at last session end:

The chat.js fix (replacing the destructured context pattern) had been committed but not yet confirmed live in production
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY environment variable needs verification that it is set under the Production scope (not Preview only) in Cloudflare Pages settings


On the horizon

Confirming the chat assistant is fully functional end-to-end in production (API key scope, proxy routing, response delivery)
Chat feature gates fitness/nutrition advice behind Standard/Premium plan via profiles.plan column — may need further testing
Conversation history: stored in Supabase for authenticated users, localStorage for anonymous users — integration stability to verify


Key learnings & principles

Cloudflare Pages Functions scope issue: Destructuring context at the top level (const { env } = context) causes bundler scope errors; always access context.env and context.request directly inside the handler
GitHub file editing pitfall: Using GitHub's web editor without selecting all (Ctrl+A) before pasting appends content, causing duplicate export errors — always replace the full file
Service Worker cache as a debugging suspect: Stale SW cache has caused multiple misdiagnoses; cache version should be bumped and SW cleared when deploying fixes
Cloudflare Pages vs. Workers: Environment variables must be set in the Pages project, not a separate Worker — easy to misconfigure via the dashboard
Supabase CDN floating tags (@2 without a pinned version) can resolve to cached incompatible builds; always pin to a specific version
Commit verification before diagnosing: Several bugs were caused by the correct file never having been committed — always confirm the repo state matches expectations before assuming a logic error
CSS nesting and DOM structure must align: CSS nesting hierarchy should reflect actual rendered DOM, not assumed structure — validate against JS-rendered output when dynamic elements are involved


Approach & patterns

José uploads files at the start of sessions for Claude to audit before making changes
Fixes are delivered as complete, downloadable file outputs (not diffs)
Bugs are worked through sequentially by priority, confirmed by José before moving on
Production issues are debugged by cross-referencing browser console errors, Cloudflare deployment logs, and repository state
Rollbacks to last stable deploy are used as a stabilisation strategy during deployment crises


Tools & resources

Cloudflare Pages — hosting and Pages Functions (serverless proxy)
Supabase — authentication, user profiles, chat history storage
Anthropic API — powers the chat assistant widget (proxied server-side)
GitHub (onitech38/HIIT-Gym) — source repository with Cloudflare CI/CD integration
Service Worker (sw.js) — PWA caching, versioned manually

